Problem: 6.3-5. Let $Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8$ be the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous-type distribution with 70 th percentile $\pi_{0.7}=27.3$.
(a) Determine $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$.
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The problem involves finding \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\) for the order statistics \(Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8\) from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\). This means \(P(X \leq 27.3) = 0.7\) for a random variable \(X\) from this distribution.

Since the distribution is continuous, \(P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(Y_7 \leq 27.3)\). The event \(Y_7 \leq 27.3\) occurs if at least 7 of the 8 observations are \(\leq 27.3\). Let \(N\) be the number of observations \(\leq 27.3\). Then \(N\) follows a binomial distribution with parameters \(n = 8\) and \(p = 0.7\), so \(N \sim \text{Binomial}(8, 0.7)\).

Thus, \(P(Y_7 \leq 27.3) = P(N \geq 7) = P(N = 7) + P(N = 8)\).

Calculate:
- \(P(N = 7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3) = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3\)
- \(P(N = 8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 = 1 \times (0.7)^8\)

Compute the powers:
- \((0.7)^7 = 0.0823543\)
- \((0.7)^8 = 0.05764801\)

Then:
- \(P(N = 7) = 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 8 \times 0.02470629 = 0.19765032\)
- \(P(N = 8) = 0.05764801\)

Sum:
- \(P(N \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833\)

Rounding to three significant figures, the result is 0.255.

