Solution: The distribution of \(Y\) is binomial with parameters \(n = 500\) and \(p = 0.25\). The goal is to find a lower bound for \(P(|Y/n - 0.25| < 0.05)\).

Using Chebyshev's inequality, for a random variable \(X\) with mean \(\mu\) and variance \(\sigma^2\), \(P(|X - \mu| \geq k\sigma) \leq 1/k^2\), so \(P(|X - \mu| < k\sigma) \geq 1 - 1/k^2\).

