Problem: 5.3-15. Three drugs are being tested for use as the treatment of a certain disease. Let $p_1, p_2$, and $p_3$ represent the probabilities of success for the respective drugs. As three patients come in, each is given one of the drugs in a random order. After $n=10$ "triples" and assuming independence, compute the probability that the maximum number of successes with one of the drugs exceeds eight if, in fact, $p_1=p_2=p_3=0.7$
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The problem requires finding the probability that the maximum number of successes for one of the three drugs exceeds eight, given that each drug has a success probability of 0.7 and there are 10 independent triples (each triple assigns one patient to each drug).

For each drug, the number of successes follows a binomial distribution with parameters \(n = 10\) and \(p = 0.7\). The probability that the maximum number of successes exceeds eight is equivalent to the probability that at least one drug has more than eight successes (i.e., 9 or 10 successes).

First, compute the probability that a single drug has more than eight successes:  
- \(P(S_i = 9) = \binom{10}{9} (0.7)^9 (0.3) = 10 \times (0.7)^9 \times 0.3\)  
- \(P(S_i = 10) = \binom{10}{10} (0.7)^{10} (0.3)^0 = (0.7)^{10}\)  

Calculating numerically:  
- \((0.7)^9 = 0.040353607\)  
- \(P(S_i = 9) = 10 \times 0.040353607 \times 0.3 = 0.121060821\)  
- \((0.7)^{10} = 0.0282475249\)  
- \(P(S_i = 10) = 0.0282475249\)  
- \(P(S_i > 8) = P(S_i = 9) + P(S_i = 10) = 0.121060821 + 0.0282475249 = 0.1493083459\)  

The probability that a single drug has at most eight successes is:  
- \(P(S_i \leq 8) = 1 - P(S_i > 8) = 1 - 0.1493083459 = 0.8506916541\)  

Since the drugs are identical and independent, the probability that all three drugs have at most eight successes is:  
- \(P(\text{all } S_i \leq 8) = [P(S_i \leq 8)]^3 = (0.8506916541)^3\)  

Calculating:  
- \((0.8506916541)^2 = 0.7236768788\)  
- \((0.8506916541)^3 = 0.7236768788 \times 0.8506916541 = 0.6156258809\)  

The probability that the maximum number of successes exceeds eight is:  
- \(P(\max S_i > 8) = 1 - P(\text{all } S_i \leq 8) = 1 - 0.6156258809 = 0.3843741191\)  

Rounded to three significant figures, this is 0.384.

Summary: The final answer is 0.384
