Solution: The probability that at least one student rolls a number matching their student number is calculated as the complement of the probability that no matches occur. Since each die is fair and independent, the probability that a specific student does not roll their own number is \( \frac{11}{12} \). For all 12 students, the probability of no matches is \( \left( \frac{11}{12} \right)^{12} \).

Thus, the probability of at least one match is:
\[
1 - \left( \frac{11}{12} \right)^{12}
\]

